%20suggested%20he%20gave%20French%20authorities%20%26quot%3Bbackdoor%26quot%3B%20access%20to%20Telegram%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20became%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20struggle%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-removes-highest-level-data-security-uk-government-backdoor-order-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Euser%20data%20privacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20social%20media%20companies%20and%20national%20governments%20after%20he%20was%20arrested%20by%20French%20authorities%20one%20year%20ago%2C%20in%20August%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEO%20was%20detained%20for%20four%20days%20and%20accused%20of%20being%20complicit%20in%20allowing%20criminal%20activity%20to%20occur%20on%20Telegram.%20He%20has%20denied%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelegram-ceo-pavel-durov-charges-questions-free-speech-censorship-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20criminal%20charges%3C%2Fa%3E%20laid%20against%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDurov%20shared%20a%20four-part%20thread%20about%20the%20ongoing%20case%20on%20X%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20anniversary%20of%20his%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20year%20ago%2C%20the%20French%20police%20detained%20me%20for%204%20days%20because%20some%20people%20I'd%20never%20heard%20of%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-telegram%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETelegram%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20coordinate%20crimes%2C%26quot%3B%20Durov%20wrote%20in%20the%20thread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BArresting%20a%20CEO%20of%20a%20major%20platform%20over%20the%20actions%20of%20its%20users%20was%20not%20only%20unprecedented%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20legally%20and%20logically%20absurd%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrench%20prosecutors%20charged%20Durov%20in%20late%20August%202024%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftelegram-ceo-pavel-durov-charges-questions-free-speech-censorship