2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-layoffs-major-round-managers-workers-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20is%20conducting%20layoffs%20again%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20anything%2C%20it's%20a%20reminder%20that%20no%20company%20is%20too%20big%20or%20too%20successful%20to%20let%20people%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENobody%20is%20ever%20secure.%20If%20you%20plan%20ahead%20and%20take%20proactive%20steps%20%E2%80%94%20like%20building%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-microsoft-worker-side-business-job-security-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esecond%20income%20stream%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20then%2C%20God%20forbid%20a%20layoff%20happens%2C%20you're%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20downsides%2C%20including%20sacrificing%20cash%20from%20your%20lifestyle%20in%20hopes%20of%20future%20returns%2C%20and%20increased%20time%20and%20energy%20demands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20it%20can%20be%20well%20worth%20it%20if%20done%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20took%20control%20over%20my%20professional%20life%20and%20finances.%20The%20layoff%20happened%2C%20but%20despite%20that%2C%20I've%20landed%20in%20a%20good%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-cutting-jobs-again-better-off-after-being-laid-off-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756112402000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a6dab3194a2d49b8aee799%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-cutting-jobs-again-better-off-after-being-laid-off-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Raheel%20Khawaja%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20Microsoft%20in%202023.%20While%20working%20there%2C%20he%20built%20alternative%20income%20streams.%20Now%2C%20he%20said%20he's%20better%20off.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzitser%40businessinsider.com%20(Joshua%20Nelken-Zitser)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-cutting-jobs-again-better-off-after-being-laid-off-2025-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Clio%20built%20its%20empire%20on%20small%20law%20firms.%20Now%20it's%20spending%20%241%20billion%20to%20buy%20a%20seat%20at%20Big%20Law's%20table.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223802%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Clio%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Jack%20Newton%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68a891ebcfc04e97619bdbe9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222852%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClio%20founder%20and%20CEO%20Jack%20Newton%3Cp%3EClio%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EClio%20just%20made%20the%20largest%20deal%20in%20legal-tech%20history%2C%20buying%20vLex%20for%20%241%20billion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThough%20Clio%20is%20far%20from%20a%20household%20name%2C%20the%20deal%20could%20wreak%20havoc%20on%20the%20legal%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClio's%20bet%20has%20two%20ambitions%3A%20bust%20up%20the%20legal-research%20duopoly%20and%20sell%20into%20larger%20law%20firms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Clio%20bought%20vLex%20for%20%241%20billion%20in%20June%2C%20it%20called%20the%20acquisition%20a%20%26quot%3Bturning%20point%20for%20the%20future%20of%20legal%20work.%26quot%3B%20So%20far%2C%20industry%20watchers%20aren't%20convinced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClio%20is%20one%20of%20legal%20tech's%20dinosaurs.%20For%20nearly%20two%20decades%2C%20it's%20sold%20the%20unglamorous%20software%20that%20law%20firms%20use%20to%20send%20invoices%20and%20track%20cases.%20The%20%243%20billion%20company%20has%20enjoyed%20a%20recent%20growth%20spurt%2C%20adding%20%24100%20million%20in%20revenue%20annually%20for%20two%20straight%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20it%20scooped%20up%2C%20vLex%2C%20is%20a%20different%20animal%3A%20a%20pioneer%20in%20legal%20research%20and%20the%20closest%20thing%20yet%20to%20a%20serious%20rival%20to%20LexisNexis%20and%20Westlaw%2C%20both%20deep%20repositories%20of%20case%20law.%20It%20built%20a%20vast%20digital%20law%20library%20and%2C%20more%20recently%2C%20layered%20in%20generative%20artificial%20intelligence%20to%20help%20lawyers%20search%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%241%20billion%20deal%2C%20the%20largest%20in%20legal%20tech%20history%2C%20sought%20to%20fuse%20these%20offerings.%20As%20Clio%20founder%20and%20chief%20executive%20Jack%20Newton%20put%20it%2C%20Clio%20handles%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebusiness%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20law%3B%20vLex%20covers%20the%20%3Cem%3Epractice%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20law.%20Together%2C%20they're%20pitching%20an%20all-in-one%20stack%20for%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20conversations%20with%20nine%20people%2C%20including%20three%20Clio%20leaders%20and%20three%20competitors%2C%20the%20acquisition%20is%20really%20chasing%20two%20goals.%20One%20is%20to%20climb%20upstream%20into%20Big%20Law%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20long%20shot%2C%20by%20many%20accounts.%20The%20other%20is%20to%20chip%20away%20at%20the%20duopoly%20in%20legal%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELexisNexis%2C%20founded%20in%201973%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eand%20Westlaw%2C%20launched%20in%201975%2C%20have%20spent%20decades%20digging%20a%20moat%20that's%20almost%20impossible%20to%20breach.%20Only%20one%20company%20has%20come%20close.%20And%20Clio%20just%20bought%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22384cc922-caa1-4729-b4b1-5f5d5808663c%5C%22%3ECracking%20the%20duopoly%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20200%2C000%20users%2C%20Clio%20has%20traction%20with%20the%20lawyers%20who%20make%20up%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20American%20bar%3A%20solos%20and%20small%20firms.%20These%20attorneys%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20run%20their%20practice%20from%20a%20desktop%20computer%2C%20still%20have%20a%20fax%20machine%20in%20the%20office%2C%20and%20often%20turn%20to%20free%20tools%20like%20Fastcase%2C%20a%20vLex%20product%2C%20for%20research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20far%20less%20likely%20to%20be%20on%20LexisNexis%20or%20Westlaw%2C%20which%20are%20priced%20for%20Big%20Law%20with%20subscriptions%20that%20can%20run%20into%20the%20tens%20of%20thousands%20a%20year.%20According%20to%20a%202024%20American%20Bar%20Association%20survey%2045%25%20of%20solo%20attorneys%20report%20using%20a%20paid%20online%20research%20tool%2C%20compared%20to%2078%25%20of%20lawyers%20at%20larger%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legal-research%20duopoly%20has%20been%20propped%20up%20by%20the%20simple%20fact%20that%20American%20law%2C%20while%20technically%20public%20domain%2C%20isn't%20freely%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFederal%20courts%20charge%20for%20access%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eto%20filings%20by%20the%20page.%20Some%20state%20courts%20offer%20recent%20opinions%20online%2C%20but%20older%20decisions%20may%20be%20stuffed%20into%20filing%20cabinets.%20Even%20when%20documents%20are%20digitized%2C%20they're%20hard%20to%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELexis%20and%20Westlaw%20solved%20that%20by%20collecting%2C%20cleaning%2C%20and%20organizing%20the%20material%20into%20usable%20form%2C%20said%20Shlomo%20Klapper%2C%20a%20former%20litigator%20turned%20legal-tech%20entrepreneur.%20They%20package%20the%20law%20and%20sell%20it%20back%20to%20lawyers%2C%20law%20schools%2C%20and%20the%20courts%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaw%20schools%20often%20give%20students%20free%20access%20to%20Lexis%20and%20Westlaw.%20Because%20lawyers%20spend%20years%20becoming%20fluent%20in%20one%20system%2C%20they're%20reluctant%20to%20switch%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20for%20the%20incumbents%20to%20set%20prices%20and%20shut%20out%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Clio%2C%20vLex%20built%20its%20base%20among%20small-time%20lawyers%20and%20says%20it%20now%20reaches%202%20million%20users%20through%20state%20bar%20associations%20that%20bundle%20in%20access.%20Joining%20forces%20gives%20them%20a%20chance%20to%20pitch%20their%20products%20to%20each%20other's%20customers%2C%20creating%20what%20could%20be%20a%20major%20cross-selling%20opportunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20small%20firms%20without%20IT%20support%2C%20an%20all-in-one%20%26quot%3Beverything%20law%20co.%26quot%3B%20is%20far%20more%20attractive%20than%20piecing%20together%20software%20from%20multiple%20vendors%2C%20said%20Adrian%20Parlow%2C%20a%20legal%20tech%20founder%20whose%20startup%2C%20PointOne%2C%20works%20to%20automate%20timekeeping%20and%20billing%20for%20law%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20vLex%20at%20its%20side%2C%20Clio%20believes%20it%20can%20loosen%20the%20grip%20on%20legal%20research.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.artificiallawyer.com%2F2025%2F07%2F01%2Fafter-vlex-more-ma-one-day-an-ipo-for-clio%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalyst%3C%2Fa%3E%20Richard%20Tromans%20put%20it%2C%20the%20bet%20is%20to%20turn%20the%20%26quot%3BBig%20Two%26quot%3B%20into%20a%20%26quot%3BBig%20Three.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Wong%2C%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Thomson%20Reuters%2C%20Westlaw's%20parent%20company%2C%20isn't%20convinced%20Clio's%20%26quot%3Bone-stop%20shop%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20serious%20threat.%20The%20idea%20of%20linking%20billing%20to%20research%20may%20offer%20small%20firms%20some%20efficiencies%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20it%20fundamentally%20changes%20how%20you%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227bec9ff7-dd7f-4783-8555-dc9cbe08cca3%5C%22%3ESelling%20upstream%20to%20Big%20Law%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhere%20the%20story%20gets%20shakier%20is%20Clio's%20other%20ambition%3A%20to%20sell%20upstream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClio%20insists%20it's%20already%20on%20the%20path.%20Chief%20operating%20officer%20Ronnie%20Gurion%2C%20a%20former%20Uber%20exec%2C%20points%20to%20more%20than%201%2C000%20mid-market%20firms%20using%20its%20software.%20He%20framed%20the%20acquisitions%20of%20vLex%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.clio.com%2Fabout%2Fpress%2Fsharedo-acquisition%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShareDo%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Clio-like%20platform%20that%20served%20many%20of%20the%20largest%20law%20firms%20in%20the%20UK%20%E2%80%94%20as%20a%20bridge%20into%20the%20highest-grossing%20firms%20and%20top-tier%20enterprises.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pitch%20is%20that%20Big%20Law%2C%20like%20smaller%20firms%2C%20will%20eventually%20prefer%20a%20single%2C%20cloud-native%20platform%20over%20a%20patchwork%20of%20tools.%20But%20making%20that%20case%20means%20persuading%20some%20of%20the%20most%20entrenched%2C%20risk-averse%20institutions%20that%20a%2017-year-old%20practice-management%20company%20is%20now%20a%20peer%20to%20the%20research%20giants%20they've%20trusted%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20tough%20sell%2C%20said%20Klapper%2C%20the%20former%20attorney%20who%20now%20runs%20Learned%20Hand%2C%20a%20company%20building%20tools%20for%20judges%20and%20clerks.%20Lawyers%20at%20larger%20firms%20prefer%20to%20cite%20established%20sources%20like%20Westlaw%20or%20Lexis%20over%20newer%20databases%2C%20even%20if%20the%20case%20text%20is%20identical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTreatises%20and%20annotations%20aren't%20just%20documents%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20symbolic%20authority%2C%26quot%3B%20Klapper%20said.%20%26quot%3BEven%20if%20duplicated%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20trusted%20without%20the%20halo%20of%20their%20provenance.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClio%20built%20its%20empire%20on%20small%20law%20firms.%20Now%20it%20hopes%20the%20%241%20billion%20it%20spent%20on%20vLex%20will%20help%20it%20buy%20a%20seat%20at%20Big%20Law's%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistory%20suggests%20Clio%20may%20not%20get%20the%20warm%20welcome%20it%20wants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amrussell%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Emrussell%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%40MeliaRussell.01.%20Use%20a%20personal%20e