quot%3Bfundamental%20limitations%20in%20how%20models%20maintain%20algorithmic%20consistency%20across%20problem%20scales.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlexandr%20Wang%2C%20the%20head%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ai-superintelligence-labs-reorg-alexandr-wang-memo-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta's%20superintelligence%20division%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20appears%20equally%20uncertain.%20He%20said%20scaling%20is%20%26quot%3Bthe%20biggest%20question%20in%20the%20industry%26quot%3B%20at%20the%20Cerebral%20Valley%20conference%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20scaling%20worked%2C%20access%20to%20high-quality%20data%20is%20limited.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hunt%20for%20unique%20data%20has%20been%20so%20fierce%20that%20leading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-data-source-solutions-openai-meta-google-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20companies%20are%20pushing%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20copyright%20violations.%20Meta%20once%20considered%20acquiring%20publisher%20Simon%20%26amp%3B%20Schuster%20as%20a%20solution.%20Anthropic%20collected%20and%20scanned%20millions%20of%20pirated%20books%20while%20training%20Claude%2C%20which%20a%20district%20judge%20ruled%20in%20June%20did%20not%20constitute%20fair%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20some%20leading%20AI%20researchers%20say%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-model-ai-explained-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elanguage%20itself%20is%20the%20limiting%20factor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that's%20why%20LLMs%20are%20not%20the%20path%20to%20AGI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLanguage%20doesn't%20exist%20in%20nature%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-godfather-top-names-possibilities-dangers-openai-chatgpt-list-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFei%20Fei%20Li%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Stanford%20professor%20famous%20for%20inventing%20ImageNet%2C%20said%20on%20an%20episode%20of%20Andreessen%20Horowitz's%20podcast%20in%20June.%20%26quot%3BHumans%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bnot%20only%20do%20we%20survive%2C%20live%2C%20and%20work%2C%20but%20we%20build%20civilization%20beyond%20language.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeCun's%20gripe%20is%20similar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20AI%20systems%20that%20can%20learn%20new%20tasks%20really%20quickly.%20They%20need%20to%20understand%20the%20physical%20world%2C%20not%20just%20text%20and%20language%20but%20the%20real%20world%2C%20have%20some%20level%20of%20common%20sense%2C%20and%20abilities%20to%20reason%20and%20plan%2C%20have%20persistent%20memory%20%E2%80%94%20all%20the%20stuff%20that%20we%20expect%20from%20intelligent%20entities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20during%20his%20talk%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22614659ac-3bd4-4ef3-a24f-f909c67ba82d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20ways%20to%20AGI%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20like%20Li%20and%20LeCun%20are%20pursuing%20an%20alternative%20to%20LLMs%2C%20called%20world%20models%2C%20that%20they%20believe%20is%20a%20better%20path%20to%20AGI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20large%20language%20models%2C%20which%20determine%20outputs%20based%20on%20statistical%20relationships%20between%20words%20and%20phrases%2C%20world%20models%20make%20predictions%20by%20simulating%20and%20learning%20from%20the%20world%20around%20them.%20These%20kinds%20of%20models%20feel%20more%20akin%20to%20how%20humans%20learn%2C%20while%20LLMs%20rely%20on%20vast%20troves%20of%20data%20that%20humans%20have%20no%20access%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComputer%20scientist%20and%20MIT%20professor%20Jay%20Wright%20Forrester%20outlined%20the%20value%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20model%20all%20the%20way%20back%20in%20a%201971%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEach%20of%20us%20uses%20models%20constantly.%20Every%20person%20in%20private%20life%20and%20in%20business%20instinctively%20uses%20models%20for%20decision-making.%20The%20mental%20images%20in%20one's%20head%20about%20one's%20surroundings%20are%20models%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BAll%20decisions%20are%20taken%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20models.%20All%20laws%20are%20passed%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20models.%20All%20executive%20actions%20are%20taken%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20models.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecent%20research%20has%20found%20that%20world%20models%20not%20only%20capture%20reality%20as%20it%20is%2C%20but%20can%20also%20simulate%20new%20environments%20and%20scenarios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202018%20paper%2C%20researchers%20David%20Ha%20and%20Jurgen%20Schmidhuber%20built%20a%20simple%20world%20model%20inspired%20by%20humans'%20cognitive%20systems.%20This%20was%20used%20to%20not%20only%20model%20hypothetical%20scenarios%2C%20but%20also%20to%20train%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraining%20agents%20in%20the%20real%20world%20is%20even%20more%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BSo%20world%20models%20that%20are%20trained%20incrementally%20to%20simulate%20reality%20may%20prove%20to%20be%20useful%20for%20transferring%20policies%20back%20to%20the%20real%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20Google's%20DeepMind%20released%20Genie%203%2C%20a%20world%20model%20that%20it%20says%20%26quot%3Bpushes%20the%20boundaries%20of%20what%20world%20models%20can%20accomplish.%26quot%3B%20It%20can%20model%20physical%20properties%20of%20the%20real%20world%2C%20like%20volcanic%20terrain%20or%20a%20dimly%20lit%20ocean.%20This%20could%20allow%20AI%20to%20make%20predictions%20based%20on%20what%20it%20learns%20from%20these%20real-world%20simulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20ideas%20in%20the%20works%2C%20too.%20Neuroscience%20models%20try%20to%20mimic%20the%20processes%20of%20the%20brain.%20Multi-agent%20models%20operate%20on%20the%20theory%20that%20multiple%20AIs%20interacting%20with%20each%20other%20is%20a%20better%20analogy%20to%20how%20humans%20function%20in%20real%20life.%20Researchers%20pursuing%20multi-agent%20models%20believe%20AGI%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20emerge%20through%20this%20kind%20of%20social%20exchange.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20there%20is%20embodied%20AI%2C%20which%20adapts%20world%20models%20into%20physical%20forms%2C%20allowing%20robots%20to%20interpret%20and%20train%20on%20the%20world%20around%20them.%20%26quot%3BRobots%20take%20in%20all%20kinds%20of%20forms%20and%20shapes%2C%26quot%3B%20Li%20said%20on%20the%20No%20Priors%20podcast%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20potential%20of%20these%20alternatives%2C%20and%20in%20particular%20world%20models%2C%20gives%20hope%20to%20even%20Marcus%2C%20the%20premier%20LLM%20doomer.%20He%20refers%20to%20world%20models%20as%20cognitive%20models%20and%20urges%20AI%20companies%20to%20pivot%20from%20LLMs%20and%20focus%20on%20these%20alternatives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20some%20ways%2C%20LLMs%20far%20exceed%20humans%2C%20but%20in%20other%20ways%2C%20they%20are%20still%20no%20match%20for%20an%20ant%2C%26quot%3B%20Marcus%20said%20in%20a%20June%20blog%20post.%20%26quot%3BWithout%20robust%20cognitive%20models%20of%20the%20world%2C%20they%20should%20never%20be%20fully%20trusted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flimits-large-language-models-chatgpt-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-openai-2025-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1756108862000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68ab92f9194a2d49b8af13a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flimits-large-language-models-chatgpt-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-openai-2025-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22OpenAI%20and%20other%20AI%20companies%20have%20attracted%20billions%20in%20the%20race%20to%20develop%20artificial%20general%20intelligence.%20It%20might%20be%20further%20away%20then%20we%20think.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22pgelli